c: 12
v: 51
t: "(The king had the woman assembled before him and) he said: \"What happened (between you and Joseph) when you sought to enjoy yourselves by him?\" They said: \"God save us! We perceived no evil at all on his part!\" And the wife of the minister said: \"Now the truth has come to light. It was I who sought to enjoy myself by him. He was indeed truthful (in all he said and true to his lord)"